{"article_id":"6hJC6p0RjmnbGMOq","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The revelation","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"that Hillary Rodham Clinton ' s private emails contained sensitive information","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"derived from spy satellites and signal intelligence","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"undercuts her defense","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"that she had no reason","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"to believe","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"she was dealing with classified information ,","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"security experts say .","depth":4},{"id":8,"text":"\" If she is so ignorant","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"that she doesn ' t recognize","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"that this type of information in the email as being classified ,","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"it just calls into question her overall competence , \"","depth":5},{"id":12,"text":"Larry Johnson , a former CIA analyst","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"trained in the rules","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"of handling government secrets ,","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"told The .","depth":5},{"id":16,"text":"As details emerge about the extent of Mrs. Clinton ' s use of personal email","depth":6},{"id":17,"text":"to exclusively conduct business as secretary of state ,","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"her defense has shifted .","depth":5},{"id":19,"text":"At first , she stated flatly","depth":6},{"id":20,"text":"that her private emails did not hold or transmit classified information .","depth":6},{"id":21,"text":"She later amended that defense","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"to claim","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"that none of the information","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"she sent by private email","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"was classified at the time","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"she sent it .","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"Now , her defenders have evolved her story further ,","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"suggesting","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"that she didn ' t know","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"information","depth":12},{"id":31,"text":"she was handling","depth":12},{"id":32,"text":"was classified","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"because it wasn ' t marked as such .","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"Pete Hoekstra , former chairman of the House Permanent Select Committee on Intelligence , wrote an op-ed","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"published Wednesday in The New York Post","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"calling the latest explanation from the Clinton camp a \" sham . \"","depth":6},{"id":37,"text":"\" The statement ignores how the process works .","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"The reason","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"government officials with security clearances are required to keep their correspondence on the appropriate government server","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"is so the material can be vetted and classified prior to hitting ' send ' to an uncleared recipient , \"","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"Mr. Hoekstra and former federal prosecutor Victoria Toensing wrote in the joint op-ed .","depth":6},{"id":42,"text":"In an interview with The Times , Mr. Hoekstra said","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"that repeating in an email classified information from a report or a secure briefing still violates regulations .","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"He recalled the extraordinary steps","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"the intelligence community took","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"when it gave him top-secret information .","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"He received the data either in a secure room in a House office , at an off-site FBI facility or on his secure phone .","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"Asked","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"whether it was possible that Mrs. Clinton dealt with top-secret material","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"but did not know it ,","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"Mr. Hoekstra answered :","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"\" Sure , it ' s always possible that you will have received information from the intelligence community","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"that they consider top secret","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"and you may not be aware of that .","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"Unlikely , but possible . \"","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"Last month , the inspectors general for the State Department and the intelligence community flatly contradicted Mrs. Clinton ' s claim","depth":4},{"id":57,"text":"that her emails did not contain national secrets .","depth":4},{"id":58,"text":"They wrote in a public joint statement","depth":5},{"id":59,"text":"that the information among thousands of emails on her private server was definitely classified at the time .","depth":5},{"id":60,"text":"\" These emails were not retroactively classified by the State Department ,","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"\"","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"the inspectors general wrote .","depth":6},{"id":63,"text":"\" Rather , these emails contained classified information","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"when they were generated","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"and ,","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"according to IC classification officials ,","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"that information remains classified today .","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"This classified information should never have been transmitted via an unclassified personal system . \"","depth":6},{"id":69,"text":"This week , I. Charles McCullough III , the intelligence community ' s inspector general , revealed","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"that not only did a small sampling of Mrs. Clinton ' s 30,000 emails","depth":12},{"id":71,"text":"turned over to State","depth":12},{"id":72,"text":"contain classified information ,","depth":11},{"id":73,"text":"but two held data","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"that were top-secret","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"- the highest classification .","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"Mr. McCullough went further .","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"The top-secret information was labeled \" SI , \"","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"which is intelligence community parlance for \" special intelligence. \"","depth":13},{"id":79,"text":"Special intelligence is intercepted communications from foreign targets .","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"In addition , the intercept came from code word \" talent keyhole , \"","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"( TK ) ,","depth":13},{"id":82,"text":"which stands for the nation ' s military satellites and their production of classified imagery and intercepted communications .","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"An intelligence spokeswoman said","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"the TK compartmental function \" protects information and activities","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"related to space-based collection of imagery , signals , measurement and signature intelligence , certain products , processing and exploitation techniques , and the design , acquisition , and operation of reconnaissance satellites . \"","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"\" TOP SECRET/SI/TK \" means her server held some of the nation ' s most sensitive information .","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"The information could have come from the National Security Agency and most certainly the National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency ,","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"experts said .","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"Mr. Johnson , the former CIA analyst , said","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"revelations about the highly sensitive nature of information in certain emails call into question the entirety of Mrs. Clinton ' s story about the private email server","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"she operated out of her home in Chappaqua , New York .","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"\" She ' s admitting","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"she lacks the knowledge and intelligence","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"to recognize classified information .","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"That ' s her defense ?","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"That she ' s stupid ? \"","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"\" I think","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"she knew","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"it was classified","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"and used it .","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"They were passing information back and forth . \"","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"The SI and TK designations mean","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"if Mrs. Clinton ' s server was hacked ,","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"\" there is the possibility","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"of compromising multiple intelligence sources , \"","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"Mr. Johnson said .","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"Because Mrs. Clinton conducted all State Department business on one server at her home ,","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"it is assumed that her aides also passed classified information on unsecure systems .","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"This is because a commercial system such as Mrs. Clinton ' s can not communicate with a secure government network","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"set up","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"to handle and protect secrets .","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"Mrs. Clinton did not use a State.gov account ,","depth":8},{"id":115,"text":"as is expected of all State Department employees .","depth":8},{"id":116,"text":"Intelligence experts said","depth":5},{"id":117,"text":"Mrs. Clinton ' s server ,","depth":7},{"id":118,"text":"which she turned over under pressure to the Justice Department this week","depth":8},{"id":119,"text":"after having vowed never to part with it ,","depth":8},{"id":120,"text":"was susceptible to hacks from adversaries such as China and Russia .","depth":6},{"id":121,"text":"Mrs. Clinton handed over 30,000 printed emails in December","depth":5},{"id":122,"text":"after the special House committee","depth":8},{"id":123,"text":"investigating the deadly 2012 attack on a U.S. diplomatic post in Benghazi , Libya ,","depth":8},{"id":124,"text":"pressed the State Department for her emails","depth":7},{"id":125,"text":"and discovered","depth":7},{"id":126,"text":"they were all on her own server .","depth":7},{"id":127,"text":"Watchdog groups ,","depth":8},{"id":128,"text":"including Judicial Watch ,","depth":8},{"id":129,"text":"have filed lawsuits","depth":8},{"id":130,"text":"to obtain the emails under the Freedom of Information Act .","depth":8},{"id":131,"text":"Prodded by a federal judge , State Department foreign service officers and , more recently , outside intelligence officials , have been sifting through the material","depth":7},{"id":132,"text":"to delete government secrets .","depth":7},{"id":133,"text":"The inspectors general estimate","depth":6},{"id":134,"text":"that hundreds of emails will be shown to contain classified information","depth":7},{"id":135,"text":"before the tedious process is complete .","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":271,"left":191,"right":270,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":191,"left":151,"right":190,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":151,"left":143,"right":150,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":143,"left":142,"right":7,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":142,"left":139,"right":141,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":139,"left":138,"right":3,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":138,"left":0,"right":137,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":137,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":141,"left":4,"right":140,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":140,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":150,"left":146,"right":149,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":146,"left":145,"right":11,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":145,"left":8,"right":144,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":144,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":149,"left":148,"right":15,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":148,"left":12,"right":147,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":13,"right":14,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":190,"left":168,"righ